datastructures.stacks

Interface Stack<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of object that the Stack will hold.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayListStack, ArrayStack, LinkedStack

    public interface Stack<T>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>
    A standard stack ADT interface that will be implemented by various kinds of stack implementations. A stack should allow for the following operations: push, pop, peek/top, retrieve count of elements, check for emptiness, clear the stack and toString(). Stacks will be made Iterable. While this might be counter-intuitive when thinking of Stacks as LIFO ADTs, it will make certain operations, such as copy-construction and equality check possible.
    Since:
    September 2013
    Author:
    Jason Filippou (jasonfil@cs.umd.edu)
